						<summary>

						<p>Slab built into the wall of Āñjanēya temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">11th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The top and bottom portions of this record are broken and lost. It mentions <hi rend="italic">mahāpradhāna</hi> Pampa-permānaḍi, his wife Jakkaladēvi and Poṭṭalakere. All other information are lost. Jakkaladēvi is described as <hi rend="italic">dānachintāmaṇi.</hi></p>						

						<p>It is in characters of the 11th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
